article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 77, St. Edward's 56
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Demond Watt had 20 points and 10 rebounds and Justin Reynolds added 15 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi defeated St. Edward's 77-56 Wednesday night. Hollis Hill added 11 points for the Islanders (3-5), who squashed an early second-half rally by St. Edward's with a 26-4 run. Khaliq Gross scored 18 points and Remy Boswell had 12 for the Hilltoppers, a Division II team which counted this game as an exhibition. Corpus Christi led 40-27 at halftime and scored the first four points of the second half before St. Edward's pulled to within 51-47 with 12:54 to play. Reynolds then scored five of the game's next seven points to spark the big run, and the Islanders went up 77-51 with 2:53 remaining. Corpus Christi outrebounded St. Edward's 44-20 and shot 50.9 percent.
